	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Polokwane – Limpopo police have appealed to the public for
any information regarding the shooting of a businessman on Tuesday morning. The 46-year-old man, who was the owner of a security company
in Flora Park, was shot in his home in front of his 11-year-old son and family helper. According to a statement released by Limpopo SAPS, the man’s
son was on his way to school on Tuesday morning when three unknown men
confronted him at the gate. They pushed the son back into the house and proceeded shove
him and the helper into the bedroom where the businessman was. Once inside, without saying a word, they shot the man
several times. The incident happened at around 07.10. Limpopo police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo
said no arrests have been made and the motive for the killing is unknown. Police are continuing to investigate and anyone with
information is requested to contact Warrant Officer Kotze at 0827448205. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  